JD Group Ltd., a South African
furniture retailer, said fiscal first-half net income increased
to 333 million rand from 231 million rand a year earlier.  Revenue in the six months ended Feb. 28 rose to 7.46
billion rand compared with 6.84 billion rand in the year-ago
period, JD Group said in a statement published today in
Johannesburg-based newspaper, Business Day. The company declared
an interim dividend of 1 rand a share.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
